> Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight's dinner extras transform into tomorrow's lunch.
> For the first meal in this 2-in-1 recipe, seared chicken is topped with a sweet
> and tangy balsamic fig sauce. It's paired with creamy, scallion-flecked mashed
> potatoes and roasted carrots. The next day, these ingredients take a trip south
> of the border and transform into tacos! Leftovers just got a whole lot more exciting.

== Mashed Potatoes and Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}; place in a #medium pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{4} into
1-inch-thick pieces on the diagonal. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{4}, separating
whites from greens. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have 3 TBSP.
Halve @Lime{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, boil potatoes over medium-high heat until tender,
about ~potatoes{15%minutes}. Drain. Melt @Butter{3%tablespoon} in same #pot{}
over low heat. Stir in half the scallion whites and cook until softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Add drained potatoes and 1 package @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon};
mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

== Blackened Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{20%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season 2 cutlets
with @Blackening Spice{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Season remaining cutlets
with only salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add all cutlets and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Rinse and wipe out
pan.

== Balsamic Fig Sauce ==

Melt 1 TBSP butter in same #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add minced shallot and
cook, stirring, until softened, about ~{1%minute}. Add @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Fig Jam{2%tablespoon}, and ¼ cup water; stir to
combine. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP
butter until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Divide potatoes, carrots, and salt-and-pepper-seasoned cutlets between plates.
Top cutlets with sauce. Garnish with half the scallion greens.

== Blackened Chicken Tacos for Lunch ==

Thinly slice blackened cutlets. In a #medium bowl{}, combine
@Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, remaining scallion whites and greens, juice from
both lime halves, and @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide
cabbage slaw between 2 #reusable containers{}. Top with chicken. Pack with
@Flour Tortillas{6}, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}, remaining sour cream, and
@Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} on the side. When ready to eat, microwave chicken until warm,
then build tacos with slaw, cheese, and condiments.